HEADWORD: Multiphase
<hw>Mul"ti*phase</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Multi-</ets> + <ets>phase</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having many
phases;</def> <specif>specif.</specif> <fld>(Elec.)</fld>,
<def>pertaining to, or designating, a generator producing, or any system
conveying or utilizing, two or more waves of pressure, or electromotive
force, not in phase with each other; polyphase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

